<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="144" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,491,338,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="144">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—So far, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etter, A. Vazquez &amp; Rosales" authorityYear="2022" box="[598,868,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Graptopetalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kristenii">
<emphasis box="[598,868,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="144">Graptopetalum kristenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from a single population in the Sierra de Coalcomán, 
<collectingRegion box="[317,445,374,400]" country="Mexico" name="Michoacan de Ocampo" pageId="8" pageNumber="144">Michoacán</collectingRegion>
. It grows in tropical deciduous forest on rocky vertical slopes along a small portion of the Río Coalcomán at an elevation between 
<quantity box="[657,788,410,437]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="144" unit="m" value="750.0" valueMax="800.0" valueMin="700.0">700–800 m</quantity>
